Center: OECD/NEA Nuclear Data Bank, Boulogne-Billancourt, France
title: -Excitation Functions and Differential Cross Sections for The Be-9(N,A)-Reaction With 8 To 30 Mev Neutrons.-

x4freetext: EXP. DESCRIPTION.
WITH A TITLE  INVESTIGATION OF THE
REACTION BE-9(N,A)HE-6 IN THE ENERGY RANGE FROM
8-30 MEV BY MEANS OF A 4 PARAMETER EXPERIMENT.
(IN GERMAN).

x4codes.shortRef: Prog: Report from Euratom-countries + Euratom to EANDC, No.127U (1970)

x4freetext: WITH S.CIERJACKS, G.J.KIROUAC,
D.KOPSCH, J.NEBE.
NUMERICAL DATA FROM KROPP.
-EXCITATION FUNCTIONS AND DIFFERENTIAL CROSS SECTIONS
FOR THE BE-9(N,A)-REACTION WITH 8 TO 30 MEV NEUTRONS.-
.KARLSRUHE ISOCHRONOUS CYCLOTRON (KIC).
.BE(D,N)-REACTION OR
C(D,N)-REACTION.
.A CONTINUOUS ENERGY SPECTRUM EVERY 90 NS BY DEUTERONS
HITTING THE CYCLOTRON BEAM STOP.
.THE PHASE WIDTH OF THE INTERNAL DEUTERON BEAM LIMITS
THE LENGTH OF THE INITIAL NEUTRON BURST TO ABOUT 1 NS.
.AT THE TARGET POSITION A NEUTRON FLUX OF AT LEAST
3.E+7 N/(MEV*CM2*SEC)IN THE SPECTRUM BETWEEN 10 AND
30 MEV WAS OBTAINED.
.METALLIC, 4.75 MILLI-G/CM2 THICK BERYLLIUM.
A 4 PARAMETER TIME OF FLIGHT EXPERIMENT(I.E.
NEUTRON ENERGY, PARTICLE ENERGY, PARTICLE TYPE AND
REACTION ANGLE).  FLIGHT PATH = 4.22 M,
TIME RESOLUTION = 3 NS.
A SET OF 4 COUNTER TELESCOPES EACH
CONSISTING OF 2 SILICON SEMICONDUCTOR DETECTORS ( 60
AND 500 MICRON THICK).
.FAST OUTPUT PULSES WERE OBTAINED FROM SEMICONDUCTORS
USING A TECHNIQUE BY PAPADOULOS,
NUCL.INSTR.METHOD 41(1966)241.
.THE DATA WERE TRANSFERRED EVENT BY EVENT VIA A CDC3100
TO MAGNETIC TAPE,
.DATA REDUCTION SUCH AS PARTICLE IDENTIFICATION AND TOF
CALCULATION WAS PERFORMED IN PART ON-LINE AND
DATA ACCUMULATION AND CROSS SECTION EVALUATION WERE
DONE OFF-LINE WITH AN IBM 7074 COMPUTER.
.PRIV.COM. DATA FROM KROPP 17/02/71.
.OVERALL NEUTRON ENERGY RESOLUTION OF 640 AND 1800 KEV
AT N-ENERGIES OF 10 AND 20 MEV OBTAINED.
.THE ERROR OF CROSS SECTION IN THE ABSOLUTE SCALE IS
ABOUT 7 TO 10 PER CENT MAINLY DUE TO COUNTING
STATISTICS AND THE ACCURACY OF THE DIFFERENTIAL N-P
CROSS SECTION.
GOLDBERG ET AL., BNL-400, 2ND ED. VOL.1 (1962),
HORSLEY ET AL.,NUCL.DATA A2(ACADEMIC PRESS INC. 1966).
ALPHA S
.INTEGRATED CROSS SECTION FROM PHI-MIN-CM = 10 DEG TO
PHI-MAX-CM (DEG) GIVEN IN THE TABLE.
.THE ERROR IS ESTIMATED TO BE ABOUT 8 TO 10 PER CENT.
